#data_testopenPromo20
def check_null_ajacent(data,columns):
    null_indexes = []
    null_indexes_length = []
    for column in columns:
        index = data[data[column].isnull()].index
        null_indexes.append(index)
        null_indexes_length.append(len(index))
    flag = 1
    for i in range(len(null_indexes)-1):
        if set(null_indexes[i])!= set(null_indexes[i+1]):
            flag = 0
    if(flag == 1):
        print('index')
    else:
        for i in range(len(null_indexes_length)):
            print(null_indexes_length[i],'\t')
    return null_indexes

def feature_normalization(data,columns):
    nor_cols=[]
    for column in columns:
        min_col = data[column].min()
        max_col = data[column].max()
        nor_col = data[column].apply(lambda x:(x - min_col)/(max_col - min_col))
        nor_cols.append(nor_col)
    data_concat = pd.concat(nor_cols,axis=1)
    return data_concat

data_train_test_complete.CompetitionDistance =  feature_normalization(data_train_test_complete,
                               ['CompetitionDistance'])

from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
from sklearn.metrics import make_scorer
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score

def mae(y_true,y_predict):
    score = mean_absolute_error(y_true,y_predict)
    return score
def mse(y_true,y_predict):
    score = mean_squared_error(y_true,y_predict)
    return score
def mape(y_true,y_predict):
    n = len(y_true)
    relative = abs(y_true - y_predict)/(1+abs(y_true))
    score = sum(relative)/n*100
    return score
def neg_mape(y_true,y_predict):
    n = len(y_true)
    relative = abs(y_true - y_predict)/(1+abs(y_true))
    score = sum(relative)/n*100
    return -score

mae_scorer = make_scorer(mae)
mse_scorer = make_scorer(mse)
mape_scorer = make_scorer(mape)
neg_mape_scorer = make_scorer(neg_mape)

def estimate(estimator, name='estimator'):
    mean_absolute_error = cross_val_score(estimator, train_x, train_y, scoring=mae_scorer, cv=5).mean()
    mean_squared_error = cross_val_score(estimator, train_x, train_y, scoring=mse_scorer, cv=5).mean()
    r2_score = cross_val_score(estimator, train_x, train_y, scoring='r2',cv=5).mean()
    mean_absolute_percent_error = cross_val_score(estimator, train_x, train_y, scoring=mape_scorer,cv=5).mean()
    print("{}: MAE:{:f}, MSE:{:f}, MAPE:{:f}%, r2_score:{:f}".format(name,mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_percent_error, r2_score))

def RFSearch(X,y):
    n_estimators = [i for i in range(2,40,4)]
    max_depth = [i for i in range(2,40,4)]
    max_features = [i/10 for i in range(4,12,2)]
    
    params = {'n_estimators':n_estimators,
              'max_depth':max_depth,
              'max_features':max_features
    }
    
    rf = RandomForestRegressor()
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(rf,param_grid = params,scoring = 'r2',cv = 5,n_jobs = 8)
    grid_result = grid_search.fit(X,y)
    print('r2_score%f,%s'%(grid_result.best_score_,grid_result.best_params_))
    return grid_search

model = RFSearch(train_x,train_y)
